name: Wandering Witch The Journey of Elaina

note_models.name: subs2srs-japanese

fields: Ever since I was young, I loved to read.
My favorite book was The Adventures of Nike.
It contained records of the witch, Nike, as she traveled around the world.
I want to go to lots of places like Nike!
Then first, you need to study to become a witch like Nike.
If I become a witch, then you'll let me travel?
Only once you're older and become a witch, okay?
I'm going to be a witch!
There was a girl who passed the magic exams at age 14--
the youngest in the history of the Peaceful Country of Robetta--
and she became an apprentice witch.
Congrats on passing your magic exams, Elaina.
The other examinees were so weak...
At this rate, it's only a matter of time before I become a full witch, huh?
In order for an apprentice witch to become a full witch,
she must study under another witch and have her acknowledge her abilities.
U-Um, I'm Elaina, and I just passed the magi--
I just passed the magic exams and--
However, it seemed the witches of this country did not find it amusing
that I was the youngest to ever pass the magic exams...
I can't do it! I'm sorry!
...and they all refused my request to be their apprentice.
At this rate, I won't be able to become a witch.
It seems a suspicious witch has settled down deep in the woods.
I heard those rumors, too. Apparently, she's called the Stardust Witch.
I went to go meet this "Stardust Witch."
I thought that if she didn't know who I was,
then maybe she'd take me on as an apprentice.
Yes. You're the girl who passed the magic exams easily at 14, right?
You're famous, for better or for worse.
Are you here to ask about becoming my apprentice? In that case--
You're going to say no, anyway, right?
I'm not the same as the Robetta witches.
It doesn't matter what kind of girl you are to me.
Please let me be your apprentice!
This is how I met the Stardust Witch--my teacher, Miss Fran.
I'm hungry. Please make something to eat.
Isn't that kind of heavy for breakfast?
Then, some of those weeds over there will do.
Aren't you giving up a little too much?
I'm going to go pick some wild vegetables.
Um, Miss Fran, I'd like you to teach me some magic...
We'll do that later. I'm off!
No matter how many days passed, Miss Fran wouldn't teach me at all.
Please go buy some from the town.
Elaina, please catch about five geckos.
I need them for my research.
Elaina, there's a spider in the bath.
Please get rid of it. It's scary...
Witches should not be picky eaters.
Why won't you teach me any magic?
With this and that, a month passed without her teaching me anything.
I've just been doing chores ever since coming here.
Do you finally feel like teaching me magic?
No, there's nothing for me to teach you.
Also, I don't feel like stew today.
This seems to be a good time...
Miss Fran, what kind of test is this?
I'll have you fight against me.
If that's what you want, then I'll send you flying!
Is she trying to kill me?
You overwhelmed everyone at the magic exams. Is that all you've got?
Let me have some more fun.
Even though you're a star student, you're nothing to write home about...
I didn't think you'd start crying...
Here are some of those butterflies you love!
I'm not the one who likes butterflies!
Look, a crown made of weeds!
Please, stop! What are you trying to do?
It looks like I overdid it a little.
You were having fun teasing me!
I wasn't having fun at all...
You were never planning on making me a witch!
I hate you! I hate you all!
Even though I believed in you and endured everything...
I believed that everything would work out...
But you're just the same as those Robetta witches!
You have no idea how hard I was working!
I just... wanted you to acknowledge me...
I knew very well how you truly felt.
You did a good job to endure it for so long.
Are you trying to trick me again?
No, I won't trick you anymore.
You know, I was doing all this because your parents asked me to.
If she keeps going like this and becomes an adult,
there might come a day when she's unable to recover...
That's why you want me to take her as my apprentice
and teach her about failures and setbacks?
Of course, we aren't asking you to do this for free, Miss Fran.
Oh, dear! I'm not a witch who can be enticed by money...
I grudgingly accepted your parents' request.
At first, I thought I'd put you through extraordinary trials
so that you would learn about setbacks.
But you never balked at working hard in order to achieve your goal,
and you understand very well how people see you.
I thought it wouldn't do any good to give you trials
because you would just endure them and rise again.
Please don't feel like all you have to do is bear with everything.
If there's something you don't like, fight it.
Be able to clearly say "No" when you need to.
Then... the reason you wouldn't teach me magic this whole time...
I was waiting for you to reach your limit.
Today's test was for the same reason.
That was the first time I'd ever been told that.
My real training started on that day.
In order to gain a lot of different experiences...
I'm hungry, so please make something to eat.
Um, what kind of harassment is this?
You told me to stop enduring things,
so I tried to be honest about my feeling like making food for you was a pain.
Is yesterday's leftover stew and some hard bread okay?
The days when I trained with Miss Fran--
...but they were very fulfilling and fun.
It's my first time beating you.
You worked hard this past year.
I don't have anything else to teach you.
The Stardust Witch officially acknowledges you as a witch.
By the way, about your witch title...
How did you come up with it?
Your hair is the color of ash.
Don't you think that's a little too simplistic?
I thought it was pretty cool, though...
By the way, why are you called "the Stardust Witch"?
Well? What do you think about "the Ashen Witch"?
Please do your best from now on.
Miss Fran told me then that she was actually a distinguished witch from another country.
Then, why did you come here?
There was someone I wanted to meet.
I wish I could stay longer,
but there are many people waiting for me back home.
Father, Mother, I've become a witch.
So please allow me to go on a journey.
You don't have to rush things, do you?
However, there are three promises you must keep.
First, if you are in trouble, run away.
Second, don't think of yourself as anyone special.
Don't forget that you're the same as everyone else.
And third, make sure you come back one day and show us that you're doing well.
It's something she decided for herself.
Let's see her off properly, okay?
Dear, you seem like you'll die of shock when Elaina gets married...
That's exactly right for a traveler.
Take this, too, just in case.
It's the same as what I'm wearing, right?
It's just in case the wind blows it away.
Then, I'll bring it with me.
Write a diary of your travels like Nike.
Let me hear your story when you come back someday.
Okay, I'll bring it with me, too.
Please look forward to hearing the story of the journey of the Ashen Witch.
And so, I set off on my journey.
As the wind blows, as my fancy led me,
I traveled here and there and experienced many things,
Who is the witch so beautiful she'd make you sigh
flying through the stark mountain range?
In this world, there are many mages.
Even if they are all called mages,
there are the novices who can only do simple magic,
and the full witches, who are at the top.
Who is the beautiful girl wearing a brooch that signals her status as a witch,
whose ashen hair flutters in the wind, shining so much with beauty and talent
that even the sun's eyes squint involuntarily?
Welcome to the Land of Mages.
You don't need to check anything?
No, since only mages can get here in the first place,
and that brooch is proof that you're a witch, Madam Ashen Witch.
As you might guess from the name, only mages can enter the Land of Mages,
so I heard that witches, as the highest ranking mages, are especially respected
and are looked upon with envious gazes and fawned over.
I've been looking forward to visiting this country.
Flying in the sky is recommended, it looks like?
Now, first, I'll look for a place to--
I can't fix this many roof tiles...!
Don't you think you should apologize first?
Oh, I'm sorry! I'm so, so sorry!
I'm fine, but what about you?
As you can see, I'm fit as a fiddle!
I'll fix the roof tiles, so please rest a bit.
Being able to do this much is normal for a witch.
Make sure you check your surroundings when you're flying.
P-P-Please, wait. Madam Witch, is there anything I can do to apologize?
Well, take care of yourself, mage-whose-name-I-do-not-know.
Now, to find a place to stay...
Oh, that place looks splendid and fine.
What if they're like, "Madam Witch, no payment is necessary.
Please, won't you grace us with your presence?"
Miss, I'm sorry, but please find a place more suitable for you to stay at.
I've been getting kicked out of every place I've tried.
It doesn't look like there are any other hotels around.
A run-down place like this should take me, right?
You're the witch from earlier! I-I'm sorry!
Are you here for retribution? You are, aren't you?
I'm sorry! Please, just spare my life... just spare my life...
A-Are you going to tear off everything below my shoulder?
I'm just looking for a place to stay.
You saved me the trouble of going to look for you.
Please enter your name in the register.
I really am sorry about earlier.
Miss Elaina, I wanted to thank you properly.
Is there anything I can do to thank you?
It'd be great if you could give me more than just the normal witch's discount.
Then, I'll take your things to your room. Here's the key...
I can't believe I lost my brooch...
That's why the other places not only didn't fawn over me,
but they also treated me coldly.
I don't see it here, either!
We've looked so much, but we still can't find it...
I can't believe I lost something so important...
What are you doing in my room?
I have a favor to ask, so I was waiting for you.
I thought I'd locked the door, though...
Heh, you forget that I work here.
Just what do you think you're doing, coming into my room without permission?!
Madam Witch, please teach me what I need to know to pass the apprentice witch exams!
Um, what's with that pose you've been doing?
This is a traditional way of prostrating yourself from my country called "dogeza."
Anyway, tell me about your situation.
She's the cute girl in the picture!
We're from a land in the east.
We came together from afar to become apprentice witches...
We worked at this hotel to save up money as we took the exams over and over...
So the two of you are still novices after all this time?
Is your sister out right now?
She passed the last exams and went back home first...
So you panicked because your dear little sister got ahead of you,
so you thought you'd ask a witch you happened to meet for help.
Well... I suppose that's how it turned out...
Well, I can teach you until I find my brooch, at least.
And so, I became Saya's teacher.
It has an unexpectedly nice ring to it.
In order for a novice to become an apprentice witch,
she must first pass a written exam.
I hate to say it, but you can pass the written test with a night of cramming.
The problem is the second test--the magic test.
You have to keep flying on your broom and exchange nonlethal attacks,
and only the one who wins in the end can pass.
She then officially becomes an apprentice witch.
I never want to take a test like that again.
Let me give it to you straight, Saya.
the likelihood of you passing the magic test is close to zero.
Don't give it to me so straight!
But since it's "close to zero," it's not zero.
First, you need to be able to maneuver your broom as well as or better than me.
Do you want it to end with you getting knocked off your broom
Shift your weight and turn adroitly.
Next are sudden breaks and starts.
After forcing the broom to a stop with your whole body,
pretend you're kicking the air and shoot back up.
Next is breaking away in midair.
After letting go of your broom in midair,
use magic to call it back to you.
If it looks like you're in danger, I'll go help you, so you can fly without worry.
Saya was able to fly about as well as me in no time.
You can do it after all...
This must be how a mother feels when she's teaching her child to fly.
to be able to do it so quickly...
What has she been doing up until now?
You practiced hard today, too, huh?
I-I didn't think it'd be mixed in...
I hate them! I mean, they grow from trees!
I am not in the habit of eating trees!
If you're a picky eater, you can't become a witch.
If you want to become an apprentice witch,
you must have the ability to endure eating even foods you don't like.
So think of this as training and eat them all.
Now, I'll use wind magic to make the fruit from that tree drop.
You must be able to use attack magic precisely.
This is an actual, slightly underhanded--I mean, clever--
trick I used in the actual magic exams.
Use wind magic to change the flow of the air
and block the way of the other examinees.
I see! Just what I'd expect from you, Miss Elaina!
I don't know what you were expecting, but try it again.
To master it, you need your body to remember how to do it.
And so, for the next few days, I searched for my brooch in between Saya's training.
It's really nowhere to be found...
I've been forgetting things a lot recently...
Oh! I remember now! I remember--
Sorry this is such a cheap place.
Anyway, you can if you want.
You've improved a lot, haven't you?
You don't need my help anymore.
I still have a lot of things I want you to teach me.
I'll be leaving this country soon.
But until then, we'll always be together.
Please teach me a lot more,
You're asking for too much, Saya.
Will you please return my brooch?
I thought it was because I was good at teaching,
You were able to ride a broom properly from the start.
You came from a faraway land, didn't you?
If you were bad at flying, then how did you get here?
Yes, when I heard what the woman said, everything made sense.
You can't tie someone down using misguided methods like this.
I'm not your little sister, you know.
I wanted to be together with someone.
I hated being alone so much... I was scared...
When you are seriously trying to accomplish something,
You can't do it if you're not alone.
Once you start being friendly, it's over.
It's hard to fight alone, isn't it?
So that you'll be fine even if you're alone,
please allow me to leave a part of me by your side.
After this, you will be by yourself.
But, you will not be alone.
People like your sister and me are all watching over you.
I'll pay for your whole hotel stay...
If I don't have enough, I'll pay in installments...
And so, we spent our last night together.
and taught her ways to make it through the magic exams.
She told me about her little sister,
and I told her of my journey.
Saya looked so fragile and helpless...
I felt like I was looking at my past self.
Six months have passed since then.
I'm now in a country far from the Land of Mages.
Examinee who successfully passed the apprentice witch exams...
The article wrote about her days of anguish and her hopes for the future.
about how she met a traveler and received courage to fight alone and a hat,
and how she finally became an apprentice witch.
When I become a full witch,
I'm going to go see the traveler that I love!
I'm waiting patiently for you as I continue on my journey, Saya.
Maybe I should've flown over the forest.
I guess I just have to keep going.
They say that beautiful flowers have thorns.
Occasionally, beautiful things will bare their fangs when you touch them.
By the way, on another note,
who is this beauty blooming as beautifully as the most colorful flowers?
What a magnificent field of flowers.
Are you the one taking care of this flower field?
There's no one taking care of this flower field.
I'm just here because I like flowers.
I'm just playing with the flowers while basking in the sun.
Then, these flowers are growing here naturally?
I wonder if I might ask a favor of you.
I'd like you to bring this bouquet to the country you are about to enter.
I don't mind, but who should I give it to?
Anyone. What's important is that someone thinks these flowers are beautiful.
In other words, you'd like me to advertise this flower field?
Very well. I'll make sure to give these to someone.
Do you have business with me?
What's with that bouquet of flowers?
You... Where did you get this?
It has nothing to do with you. Please return it.
I'll take care of the rest. You go back.
Sir, this shawl... and these flowers... They might be--
Recently, his younger sister went missing,
and he's been like that ever since.
By the way, sorry, but will you let us dispose of those flowers?
They are not allowed into this country.
They won't do anything to a witch,
but there's magic in them that will make people who can't use magic go insane.
Yes, people who are mesmerized by the flowers
are drawn to them like bees to honey
and led to where the flowers bloom, becoming nutrients for them to feed off of.
That's why you must dispose of them?
Sorry about this. You can go.
In my favorite book, The Adventures of Nik,
there is a story about a strange plant.
Normally, plants release magic for us after absorbing sunlight.
But, through a sudden mutation, it started sucking magic,
became sentient, and started acting violently. That's what the story was about.
The next day, before I left for the next country,
I went to the flower field I had visited the day before.
There was something I wanted to check.
...thanks to your bringing her shawl and that bouquet.
I figured out that she was here...
Trying to keep such a wonderful place to yourself...
Come on, let's show this place to everyone in the country, too.
Besides, I want to show you off now that you've become as pretty as a flower.
You're a real witch! That's amazing!
What're you doing in a place like this?
It's a bottle where I'm gathering happiness.
I turn the moments people and animals feel happiness into magic
and put them into this bottle!
So you can use magic, too?
Are you changing feelings into magic?
If you open this here, then my hard work will come to nothing.
These are precious treasures I've been gathering for the girl I like.
It reminded me of a book I read in the past.
For the sake of his wife, who was sick and couldn't leave the house,
a husband travels around the world,
so he could bring them home and show them to his wife.
I bet his wife was really happy!
I'm sure she was healed and lived a long life!
So, who's this girl you like?
She's a servant named Nino who works at my house.
She always looks gloomy, so I want to cheer her up.
That's why I'm bottling up happiness.
Yeah! I tried to see if I could get happiness from them, but it didn't really work.
You're lucky the plants didn't use you for food.
Oh, you can see it up ahead!
Is that the village chief's house?
You don't seem that interested, Miss Witch.
Would it be better for me to act surprised?
Wow, that's amazing! You're rich, aren't you?
When will you give her that bottle?
I think I'll give it to her after we finish lunch.
Oh, right! Why don't you come eat lunch with us?
The food Nino makes is really good!
Thank you for the invitation, but I just ate breakfast.
Then, I'll make sure you get a smaller portion.
Are there any foods you don't like or can't eat?
Got it. I'll make sure she doesn't put any in.
Please make sure it's a small portion.
The food'll definitely be really delicious--
Could you be from a land in the east? Huh? U-Um...
Oh, you just seemed similar to someone I know.
My dad found her in an eastern land.
The village chief is... very kind...
Hey, hey, Nino! What's for lunch today?
T-Today, the village chief said he wants... fish grilled with salt...
Can you make some for Miss Witch over there, too?
But please don't give me too much.
I have a present for you after lunch.
The village chief will be angry.
Don't worry about it! I'll explain to Dad.
Then, this is an order from me:
You can have a seat, Miss Witch.
We'll take care of the food.
Oh? It's unusual for us to have a guest.
I am the traveling witch, Elaina.
Thank you for the food. It was very good.
Oh, don't worry about it, Miss Witch.
You met Nino in a land in the east?
A few years ago, my wife left.
There was a period when we had problems getting the housework done.
I found her in an eastern land when I was there for work around that time.
She was expensive, but she could do some housework,
and most of all, she is sure to be a beauty when she grows up,
so I bought her without any hesitation.
As I thought, she's a great servant.
but he doesn't care if the other person is a slave or what.
Hey, Nino, where should I put the big plat--
How long will it take before you learn to do your job perfectly?!
Hurry up and clean it up!
That was my fault just now. Nino didn't--
You don't need to clean it up.
Next time, be careful not to drop it.
For you to see something so disgraceful, and then even fixing the china for us...
Come on, you thank her properly, too.
At times like this, you should say "Thank you."
I could've done magic like that.
Speaking of which, Nino seems very depressed right now, doesn't she?
Isn't this the perfect time to give her present to her?
Miss Witch, you might be a genius!
Feel free to praise me more.
I said earlier that I had a present for you, right?
This is a bottle filled with happiness.
It's filled with the happiness of various people I found in various places.
You can only see it once, so look carefully.
The outside world is filled with all this happiness.
So don't always look so gloomy.
Nino and I will make food that's even more delicious for you! Right?
Yes, I'll come back and visit.
It was then that I remembered the ending of the book I read in the past--
The beautiful scenes the husband brought home
ended up making his wife, who couldn't go anywhere, even more depressed.
Just because you are doing something for someone else doesn't make it right.
It was a really preachy story.
Kindness and beauty can sometimes become cruel.
I don't know what happened to Nino after that.
No, I don't want to know...
This is a story about love.
The princess of a certain country fell in love.
The person she fell in love with was the castle cook.
Theirs was a love between people of different social classes.
This is off topic, but why do we say "fall in love"?
Is it because one falls into it unexpectedly and suddenly, like a pitfall trap?
The two of them nurtured their love secretly,
and in time, the princess became pregnant.
Yes, it was the fruit of their love, so to speak.
I wonder if there was a war or something.
I didn't hear anything about that, though.
There isn't a single person here...
Even if I head to another town now,
I probably won't get there until the middle of the night...
This is the only place that looks like it's still standing...
It looks like no one's home.
I am very reluctant to do this, but I have to do what I have to do.
It was cold outside, wasn't it?
At any rate, I didn't think anyone lived here.
I didn't think anyone would come here, either.
My name is Miraros. Nice to meet you.
Miraros, what happened to this town?
I don't know what happened to this town, or why I'm here.
When I woke up, I found myself in this country that was already in ruins.
You who are reading this are the princess, Miraros.
You're living in a room like this in the castle,
so I guess it makes sense.
If you do not want to die, then read this."
Whoever wrote this seems pretty self-important.
It looks like the sun has set.
The next part of the letter says,
It is going wild looking for the last person--
Javalier is trying to kill me.
Then, why don't you leave this country and go somewhere else?
And then finally, it says, "I'd like to ask you a favor.
I want you to kill Javalier.
As a witch, you should have enough power to easily defeat Javalier.
Please, for our sake, in order for you to live,
and for the sake of those unfortunate enough to be killed."
So you're a witch, too, Elaina?
That should've been obvious by my appearance.
I have my brooch on, too.
But that letter leaves a lot of questions.
Why were you the only one to survive and lose your memory?
It doesn't say anything about that.
But I'm the princess, and this country was destroyed by that monster.
So, I have a duty to defeat that.
How many days have you seen that monster?
But, I will fight it tomorrow night.
Do you have any chance of winning?
It's been one week since I woke up,
and I finally remembered how to use magic.
It's possible that before I lost my memory, I was pretty good.
Moreover, my magic has been recharged.
I will be cheering you on from a safe distance.
Oh my, you won't help me?
Will I gain anything by helping you?
And so, Miraros let me use a room once used by a castle servant.
I don't know why, but my body just seems to remember.
Anyway, let's eat while they're still warm.
Will you listen to me talk while we eat? About tonight.
I'd like you to help me prepare.
You let me spend the night and even made breakfast.
I can at least help with your preparations.
Then, will you help me fight Javalier?
Besides, if this place is safe, like the letter says,
then don't you have the choice of not fighting?
Well, I suppose the letter's credibility is also questionable, though.
The resentment the writer of that letter felt for Javalier is real.
I hate Javalier so much. I want to kill it.
And for some reason, I feel the same way.
Well? Do you think you'll finish by nightfall?
Wh-What does "finish" mean in this case?
Let's see. I think you're maybe halfway done?
Miraros's plan is to trick Javalier into falling into the hole
and then attack with magic after it is unable to move.
I see. Even if just prevents a counterattack, it could be very effective.
The flaw in this plan is that the preparations are a huge pain.
This is nothing! I'm the Ashen Witch! This is a trifle!
Thank you for your efforts. It's almost time.
I'll treat you to a delicious dinner.
It will be a lot of work for you to cook after finishing a big job,
Even though I only met her yesterday,
I couldn't help but feel like I wanted her to live.
So I will fight with her, too. Without putting my life in danger.
Maybe I won't need to do anything...
Well? Do you understand my despair now?
She told her father, the king, about how she had become pregnant with the cook's child.
This is what the king said:
The king would not allow their love that crossed class and rank.
and was burned to death in front of her eyes.
First, in order to make this castle a safe place,
I put up a barrier that only let mages in.
That's why Javalier couldn't get into the castle?
And then, I left myself a letter,
and cursed my father, turning him into a monster.
In exchange, I lost my memories.
Your father, Javalier, destroyed the country and its people...
On top of that, he did it while still aware that he was the king.
That monster ate the subjects whether the king wished to or not.
That should have made him understand how it felt...
...to have the things dear to you snatched away from you...
Okay, the bread's done. It's time to eat.
How is it? Is it good?
It can't compare to the bread you bake, though.
Do you want to eat more?
Oh, look, you've got jam on your cheek.
In this way, the curtain fell on the "love story"
that all went according to her plan.
She became the princess without subjects by her own hand...
I wonder if it's like The Adventures of Nik?
It's not just that the name is the same as Miss Fran's--
I feel like the face here looks like her, too...
As I looked at that book,
I remembered a country I stopped by six months before.
It was a big country, far away from here--
The mages are doing tricks for everyone to enjoy.
I didn't know they had a place like this...
I wonder if it's okay to go in?
Oh, I'm sorry. You're a witch?
Don't worry about it. Well then, please excuse me.
No one is allowed inside without permission.
He could've at least let me look around a little bit...
Anyway, I guess I'll look for a place to stay.
I wonder if that person is delivering newspapers?
The mages in this country are...
Hello. You're the Ashen Witch, right?
W-We're students at the Royal Magic Academy.
Are you students from the school I was at earlier?
What business do you have with me?
U-Um, will you come with us without asking any questions?
I-I said without asking any questi--
Just trust me and come with us, please.
Hey, guys, let's do this as a team.
Don't take all the glory for yourself!
I don't know what's going on, but...
You guys go toward the river.
